<1ST_LINE>d a BC-Dance     10-01 0368</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Dance,0384</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Gregory and Bujones Dance Excitingly</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: No PMs Planned</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By MARY CAMPBELL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Cynthia Gregory and Fernando Bujones, two of
America's most exciting ballet dancers, are at the City Center this
week in a program called ``Cynthia Gregory & Fernando Bujones
Together!''
   The week was almost sold out before it began by fans of Miss
Gregory, a Los Angeles native who celebrated 20 years with American
Ballet Theater in 1985, and Miami-born Bujones, former member of
American Ballet Theater. Followers of that company wish it would
invite him to return.
   The two dancers have tentative plans to tour early next year.
   The evening on Thursday began with a most charming ballet, ``The
Rehearsal.'' On a stage set to look like a rehearsal hall, Ian
Horvath, formerly of Ballet Theater and now producing director of
the Jose Limon Dance Foundation, is directing a corps de ballet.
   Miss Gregory and Bujones do the lovers' first meeting in
``Giselle,'' a kitchen scene from ``Miss Julie,'' a duet from ``La
Sylphide,'' dancing more and more excitingly. They finish with a
duet from ``Don Quixote'' in which her technique was diamond sharp
and his dazzling dancing pushed up viewers' blood pressure.
   Donald Saddler created and staged ``The Rehearsal'' and Robert
W. Larkin wrote it.
   ``Beloved - Memories'' was choreographed for four couples by
Francis Patrelle. It was meant to be exotic and turned out banal,
but the four couples danced marvelously. ``Concertino,'' in two
brief movements, one showing a mood of anxiety and one of cheer,
was choreographed for Miss Gregory and Bujones by Lynne
Taylor-Corbett.
   The only dance not new for this engagement was the Act 3 wedding
from ``Coppelia.'' Miss Gregory had plenty of chances to balance on
one toe, standing as though that were easy and coming out of it
with perfect grace. She is a rarity, a ballerina whose technique is
crystal clear yet who conveys warmth. She always had the clarity
and has grown into the warmth.
   Bujones was exciting, flying through the sky with bravura yet
not looking like an egomaniac. The last time Miss Gregory and
Bujones danced together before this week was in 1985, in
``Coppelia.''
</TEXT>
