<HEAD>Gorbachev Elected President</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   MOSCOW: who retired.
   Gromyko, 79, retired from the presidency today, a day after he
stepped down as a member of the ruling Communist Party Politburo
during a hastily called meeting of the 300-member Communist Party
Central Committee.
   That meeting approved wide-scale changes in the party
bureaucracy.
   The election of Gorbachev allowed him to unify the top Communist
Party and government jobs, increasing his power to reform the
top-heavy Soviet political system.
   Moscow Communist Party leader Lev N. Zaikov said Gorbachev had
been endorsed by the Presidium of the Supreme Soviet, and the
Central Committee of the Communist Party.
   He was elected unanimously by the 1,500-member Supreme Soviet.
