<2ND_LINE>AM-VP Debate,110</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Quayle Gets First Question in Debate</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   GOP vice presidential nominee Dan Quayle will
receive the first question and give the first closing statement in
the debate Wednesday night with Democratic opponent Lloyd Bentsen
in Omaha, Neb.
   The order _ the same as in last Sunday's presidential debate
between Republican George Bush and Democrat Michael Dukakis _ was
decided by a coin toss between Quayle and Bentsen representatives.
   The Commission on Presidential Debates, the sponsor of the
event, said the moderator will be Judy Woodruff of public
broadcasting's MacNeil@Lehrer NewsHour.
   Panelists will be Tom Brokaw of NBC, Jon Margolis of the Chicago
Tribune and Britt Hume of ABC News.
</TEXT>
