<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--UPS Driver,0184</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Another UPS Driver Nabs Robbery Suspect</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ENGLEWOOD, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   For the second time in four months in
the Denver area, a United Parcel Service driver has foiled the
getaway of a suspected robber, police said.
   UPS driver Jeff Pryor was stopped at a traffic light Thursday
when he saw a suspected thief fleeing a jewelry store, said officer
Gordon Madonna.
   Pryor jumped out of his truck, chased the man and held him until
police could arrive, Madonna said.
   ``Without the UPS guy, the (suspect) would have gotten away,''
Madonna said.
   Police in Mountain View expressed similar sentiments in June
when another UPS driver, Tom Swartz, used his truck to ram a
getaway car being used by three people who robbed a store.
   Swartz at first was threatened with disciplinary action by UPS,
but later was honored as a hero.
   In Thursday's incident, a man took a $14,000 Rolex watch from
Williams Jewelers and ran, Madonna said. A store clerk chased the
man but was losing sight of him when Pryor joined in the chase.
</TEXT>
