<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Twisted Rhymes,0149</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Frightening Kids With Scary Rhymes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MINEOLA, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police are looking for a man in a van who
has been scaring schoolchildren with twisted, threatening versions
of nursery rhymes.
   One rhyme was ``Hickory, Dickory Dock, It's 3 o'clock. I will
kill you tonight,'' police said.
   ``He has not touched the kids, or used obscene language. But he
is frightening them,'' said Nassau County Detective Lt. Gary Engles.
   The man has reportedly approached children around the age of 10
near schools in the Hewlett, Woodmere, and Valley Stream areas of
the county on Long Island four times between Sept. 13 and Sept. 27,
Engles said.
   He has engaged the children in conversations, taken pictures of
them and then recited the rhymes, police said.
   But during his conversations the blond man in his late 20s has
never left the white van.
</TEXT>
